TY  - JOUR
AU  - Lester, Benjamin
AU  - Postlewaite, Andrew
AU  - Wright, Randall
T1  - Information, Liquidity, Asset Prices, and Monetary Policy
PY  - 2012
Y1  - 2012/07/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rds003
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 79
IS  - 3
SP  - 1209
EP  - 1238
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - What determines which assets are used in transactions? We develop a framework where the extent to which assets are recognizable determines the extent to which they are acceptable in exchange—i.e. it determines their liquidity. Recognizability and liquidity are endogenized by allowing agents to invest in information. We analyse the effects of monetary policy. There can be multiple equilibria, with different transaction patterns, and these patterns are not invariant to policy. We show that small changes in information may generate large responses in asset prices, allocations, and welfare. We also discuss some issues in international economics, including exchange rates and dollarization.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rds003
ER  - 



